# Volcanic Ash Leachate Visualizer

A client-side web tool for comparing user-supplied volcanic ash leachate data to a global reference dataset (min, median, max per element). All computation is performed entirely in the user’s browser. No data are uploaded or stored.

---

## Features
- CSV upload or copy/paste input
- Filters for Magmatic Composition and Leachate Method
- Two simultaneous plots:
  • Normalized (0–100% of global min–max range)  
  • Absolute values (log scale by default, with a linear toggle)
- Colorblind-safe palette option (Okabe–Ito)
- Element ordering options (A→Z, Z→A, by global median, by user median)
- PNG export for each plot
- Auto-generated Methods paragraph

---

## Accepted CSV Columns
Case-insensitive:

- Sample  
- Element  
- Value  (or use Min and Max for ranges)  
- MagmaType  (Basalt, Basaltic andesite, Andesite, Dacite, Rhyolite)  
- Method  (e.g., RatioA, RatioB, RatioC)

Example datasets are located in the `example/` folder.

---

## Global Dataset File
The global reference dataset is stored in:

data/global_leachate_stats.json

This file contains:
- The database name
- A version string
- Min, median, max for each element
- Optional branching by magma composition and/or leachate method

https://daviddamby.github.io/ash-leachate-tool/

